        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "A new programme “Women&amp;#39;s Instinct for Developing and Ushering in Scientific Heights &amp;amp; Innovations (WIDUSHI)” is started by the Department of Science and Technology (DST) under its umbrella scheme “Women in Science and Engineering-KIRAN (WISE-KIRAN)” for senior women scientists to harness their knowledge and potential for the betterment of Science and Society. WIDUSHI programme aims to encourage and support senior women scientists to conduct research in interdisciplinary areas of Science and Technology.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "&gt; **Category A:**\n\n\n  - **Fellowship (Principal Investigator):** ₹75,000/- per month  - **Research Assistant:** 1 position provided  - **Research Grant:** ₹5,00,000 per year  - **Institutional Overhead Charges:** ₹1,00,000/- per annum\n&gt; **Category B:**\n\n\n  - **Fellowship (Principal Investigator):** ₹85,000/- per month  - **Research Assistant:** 1 position provided  - **Research Grant:** ₹5,00,000 per year  - **Institutional Overhead Charges:** ₹1,00,000/- per annum\n<br>\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "'WIDUSHI' programme aims to encourage and support senior women scientists to conduct research in interdisciplinary areas of Science and Technology.",
        "detailedDescription": [
