      "eligibilityCriteria": {
        "eligibilityDescription_md": "&gt; **Category A: The following are the primary eligibility criteria-**\n\n\n   1. **Employment:** Women Scientists who are permanent employees but retiring in a year or already retired/superannuated from government academic/research institutions.   1. **Age:** 57-62 years   1. **Qualification:** Women Scientists having Ph.D. in Basic/Applied Sciences or equivalent degree.   1. **Research Experience:** Minimum 2 R&amp;amp;D projects as Principal Investigator with excellent track record.   1. **Publications:** Minimum 20 research publications with impact factor.\n&gt; **Category B: The following are the primary eligibility criteria-**\n\n\n   1. **Employment:** Women who are not permanent employees in any institution but working temporarily and have completed 2 independent research projects as Principal Investigator.   1. **Age:** 45-62 years   1. **Qualification:** Women Scientists having Ph.D. in Basic/Applied Sciences or equivalent degree.   1. **Research Experience:** Minimum 2 R&amp;amp;D projects as Principal Investigator with excellent track record.   1. **Publications:** Minimum 10 research publications with impact factor.\n&amp;gt; **Proposals are invited from senior women scientists in the following scientific disciplines:**\n\n\n   1. Physical &amp;amp;amp; Mathematical Sciences\n   1. Chemical Sciences\n   1. Life Sciences\n   1. Earth &amp;amp;amp; Atmospheric Sciences\n   1. Engineering &amp;amp;amp; Technology\n   1. S&amp;amp;amp;T-based Societal Research\n\n&gt; **Co-Investigator (Co-I):** \n\n&amp;#39;WIDUSHI&amp;#39; fellow should choose a permanent faculty as Co-I (male/female) of the project for academic and administrative support in project implementation. The service of Co-I has to be due for a period not less than the proposed period of the WIDUSHI project. The Co-I is not eligible for any separate grants under the programme.\n<br>\n\n",
